Decision Tree Classifier:¶

In [130]:
class DecisionNode():
    # we created a desicion node class this node will include a pointer to left and right nodes
    # it will have the threShold which is our condition variable the infoGain and the index of the node
    def __init__(self, leftNode, rightNode, gini, threShold, index, value):

        self.leftNode = leftNode
        self.rightNode = rightNode
        self.gini = gini
        self.threShold = threShold
        self.index = index
        self.value = value
    



class DTC():
    def __init__(self, min_samples_split=5, depth=3):
        ''' constructor '''
        self.root = None
        # stopping conditions
        self.min_samples_split = min_samples_split
        self.depth = depth

    def build_tree(self,X,Y, depth=0):
        ''' recursive function to build the tree '''
        self.samples = len(Y)
        feature1,features = np.shape(X)
        dataset = np.concatenate((X,Y), axis=1)
        if depth <= self.depth:
            if feature1 >= self.min_samples_split:
                #we need to find the best split and save it inside this array that we created
                # 0 for left 1 for right 2 for threshold 3 for index and 4 for the gini
                split = [0, 1, 2, 3, 4]
                max_parent_gini = 1 # we need the biggest information gain and the information gain is always >=0
                # loop over all the features
                for i in range(features):#i for the index to go through all of the features
                    # loop over all the feature values present in the data
                    threSholds=dataset[:, [i,7]]
                    threSholds = threSholds[threSholds[:, 0].argsort()]
                    x1,y1=0,0
                    x2=0#how many B we have
                    y2=0
                    Y=np.array(Y)
                    
                    for y in Y:
                        if(y==1):
                            x2+=1
                        else:
                            y2+=1
                        
                    last_num=None
                    for index in range(threSholds.shape[0]):
                        if(threSholds[index][1]==1):
                            x1+=1
                            x2-=1
                        if(threSholds[index][1]==0):
                            y1+=1
                            y2-=1
                        if(last_num==None or last_num!=threSholds[index][0]):
                            parent_gini=self.child_gini(x1,y1,x2,y2)

                            if parent_gini < max_parent_gini:
                                max_parent_gini=parent_gini
                                split[2] = last_num
                                split[3] = i
                                split[4] = parent_gini
                                max_parent_gini = parent_gini#and update the max parent gini variable
                            last_num=threSholds[index][0]
                if(split[2] is not None):
                    left = np.array([row for row in dataset if row[split[3]] <= split[2]])
                    right = np.array([row for row in dataset if row[split[3]] > split[2]])
                    split[0] = left
                    split[1] = right
                    # check if information gain is positive
                    if split[4] > 0:
                        # recur left
                        left_subtree = self.build_tree(split[0][: , :-1],split[0][:, -1:],depth + 1)
                        # recur right
                        right_subtree = self.build_tree (split[1][: , :-1] , split[1][:, -1:], depth + 1)
                        # return decision node
                        return DecisionNode(left_subtree, right_subtree, split[4], split[2],
                                            split[3], None)
        Y = list(Y)
        leaf= max(Y, key=Y.count)
        return DecisionNode(None, None, None, None, None, leaf)

    def child_gini(self,x1,y1,x2,y2):
        left_gini=1
        right_gini=1
        if (x1+y1)!=0:
            left_gini-=(((x1)/(x1+y1))**2)
            left_gini-=(((y1)/(x1+y1))**2)
        else:
            left_gini=0
        if (x2+y2)!=0:
            right_gini-=(((x2)/(x2+y2))**2)
            right_gini-=(((y2)/(x2+y2))**2)
        else:
            right_gini=0
        toReturn=((x1+y1)/(x1+y1+x2+y2))*left_gini+((x2+y2)/(x1+y1+x2+y2))*right_gini
        return toReturn


    def print_tree(self, tree=None, indent=" "):
        if not tree:
            tree = self.root

        if tree.value != None:
            print(tree.value)

        else:
            print("X_" + train_X.columns[tree.index], "<=", tree.threShold, "?", round(tree.gini,3))
            print("%sleft:" % (indent), end="")
            self.print_tree(tree.leftNode, indent + indent)
            print("%sright:" % (indent), end="")
            self.print_tree(tree.rightNode, indent + indent)

    def fit(self, X, Y):
        self.root = self.build_tree(train_X,train_Y)#save the tree in the root

    def predict(self, X):
        return np.array([self.make_prediction(x,self.root) for x in X.to_numpy()])

    def make_prediction(self, x, tree):
        if tree.leftNode == None and tree.rightNode == None:
            return tree.value
        if float(x[tree.index]) <= float(tree.threShold):
            return self.make_prediction(x,tree.leftNode)
        else:
            return self.make_prediction(x,tree.rightNode)

    c = DTC(depth = depth)
    c.fit(train_X, train_Y)

    acc =accuracy_score(val_Y, y_val_pred)
    
    grid_search["max_depth"].append(depth)
    grid_search["accuracy"].append(acc)
    print('Iteration ',depth)

Sensitivity and Specifity¶

manual implamentation¶

In [235]:
def confusion_matrix(true,pred): 
    matrix=np.zeros((2,2)) 
    for i in range(len(pred)):
        #1=positive, 0=negative
        if true[i] == pred[i]:
            if pred[i] == 1:
                matrix[0,0]+=1 #True Positives
            else:
                 matrix[1,1]+=1 #True Negatives
        else:
            if pred[i] == 1:
                matrix[0,1]+=1 #False Positives
            else:
                matrix[1,0]+=1 #False Negatives
    print(matrix)        
    sensitivity=matrix[0,0]/(matrix[0,0]+matrix[1,0])
    print("Sensitivity:",sensitivity*100,'%')
    
    specificity=matrix[1,1]/(matrix[0,1]+matrix[1,1])
    print("Specificity:",specificity*100,'%')
    return sensitivity, specificity

[ 186  164   69 2094]
In [243]:
specifity = tn / (tn+fp)
sensitivity = tp/(tp+fn)
print('specifity', specifity, "  sensitivity",sensitivity) 

specifity 0.5314285714285715   sensitivity 0.9680998613037448

There is a significant difference between them, and that is due to the cutoff point (lowering the cutoff point will sensitivity higher and specificity is reduced and vice versa)¶

The optimal cutoff point is the point where there is high true positive rate (sensitivity) and low false positive rate (specifity)¶
